File: South African billionaire Patrice Motsepe. JOHANNESBURG - The Blue Bulls Rugby Union have welcomed Patrice Motsepe into their organisation. The high profile business tycoon Motsepe bought a 37 percent stake in the Union. READ: Motsepe donates R100m for job creation His part-ownership adds to his growing sporting portfolio. Motsepe owns successful local football club Mamelodi Sundowns, whom he has transformed into a force in the African game. The latest move by the Bulls means Motsepe is the joint-majority shareholder, along with Investment company Remgro